   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>CHAPTER TWO ONE SPIRIT Scripture Reading: Eph 4:3-4a; 1 Cor 12:13 OUTLINE The Spirit of God in God's creation Gen 1:2.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>The Spirit of Jehovah in God's relationship with man Num 11:29; Judg.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>3:10.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>The Spirit of holiness in the life of God's people in the Old Testament Psa 51:11; Isa 63:10-11.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>The Holy Spirit Luke 1:35; Matt 1:18: From Christ's incarnation and onward.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Making man as holy as God.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>For man to be joined to God as one.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>The Spirit for the believers of Christ in God's New Testament economy: Was not yet before Jesus was glorified John 7:39.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>The last Adam Jesus Christ became the Spirit through His resurrection 1 Cor 15:45b.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>The all-inclusive Spirit: The compound Spirit cf.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>Exo 30:23-28 , compounded with: Christ's divinity.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>Christ's humanity.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>The effectiveness of Christ's death Rom 8:13b.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>The power of Christ's resurrection Phil 3:10.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>The anointing Spirit 2 Cor 1:21-22; 1 John 2:20, 27.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>The indwelling Spirit Rom 8:11.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>The life-giving Spirit 1 Cor 15:45b; 2 Cor 3:6b.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>The Spirit of life Rom 8:2.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>The Spirit of power Luke 24:49; Acts 1:8.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>The Spirit of Jesus in His humanity with His suffering Acts 16:7.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>The Spirit of Christ in His divinity with His resurrection Rom 8:9b.</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>The Spirit of Jesus Christ in both His suffering and resurrection Phil 1:19b.</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>The Spirit of the Lord 2 Cor 3:17-18: The Lord Spirit.</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>In the transformation of the believers of Christ.</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>The consummated Spirit the Third of the consummated Triune God Rev 22:17; Matt 28:19.</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>The Spirit as the consummation of the processed and consummated Triune God John 7:39; Rev 22:17.</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>In this one Spirit 1 Cor 12:13: The believers in Christ were all baptized into one Body.</S>
   <S PAR='28' RSNT='1' SNO='28'>They were all given to drink one Spirit.</S>
   <S PAR='29' RSNT='1' SNO='29'>The Spirit of the Body Eph 4:4-6, 11-16: As the essence of the Body.</S>
   <S PAR='30' RSNT='1' SNO='30'>With the Lord as the element of the Body.</S>
   <S PAR='31' RSNT='1' SNO='31'>With God the Father as the source of the Body.</S>
   <S PAR='32' RSNT='1' SNO='32'>For the organic building up of the Body.</S>
   <S PAR='33' RSNT='1' SNO='33'>With one Bible as the one divine revelation.</S>
   <S PAR='34' RSNT='1' SNO='34'>In one teaching: The teaching of the apostles concerning God's economy Acts 2:42; 1 Tim 1:3-4.</S>
   <S PAR='35' RSNT='1' SNO='35'>According to the entire New Testament Rev 22:18-19.</S>
   <S PAR='36' RSNT='1' SNO='36'>With the base of the Old Testament 2 Tim 3:16-17.</S>
   <S PAR='37' RSNT='1' SNO='37'>Through one ministry 2 Cor 4:1: The New Testament ministry of all the New Testament ministers 2 Cor 3:8-9, 6; 1 Tim 1:12.</S>
   <S PAR='38' RSNT='1' SNO='38'>For the building up of the Body of Christ Eph 4:12, 16.</S>
   </TEXT>
